                                            <img src="//wikitravel.org/customHP/uploads/des_month/371_1699210663.jpg" alt="Heidelberg" />
                                            <h2 class="subHeading"><a href="https://wikitravel.org/en/Heidelberg">Destination of the Month</a></h2>
                                            <h3 class="buenos-aires"><a href="https://wikitravel.org/en/Heidelberg">Heidelberg</a></h3>
                                            <div class="info">
                                                <div class="info-holder">
                                                    <div class="info-frame">
                                                        <p>Heidelberg, a jewel among German travel destinations, is in the Neckar river valley right where the legend-rich Odenwald (Forest of Odes or Odin) opens up towards the plains of the Rhine Valley.</p>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>

                                                                            <div class="slide">
                                            <img src="//wikitravel.org/customHP/uploads/des_month/368_1697366899.jpg" alt="Salta" />
                                            <h2 class="subHeading"><a href="https://wikitravel.org/en/Salta">Off the Beaten Path</a></h2>
                                            <h3 class="buenos-aires"><a href="https://wikitravel.org/en/Salta">Salta</a></h3>
                                            <div class="info">
                                                <div class="info-holder">
                                                    <div class="info-frame">
                                                        <p>Salta - One of the most beautiful colonial cities in Argentina, Salta is a very hospitable place and an excellent starting point for excursions to the nearby mountains in the north-west of the South American country.</p>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>

                                                                            <div class="slide">
                                            <img src="//wikitravel.org/customHP/uploads/des_month/354_1688409672.jpg" alt="Italian Capital of Culture 2023" />
                                            <h2 class="subHeading"><a href="https://wikitravel.org/en/Brescia">Capital of Culture</a></h2>
                                            <h3 class="buenos-aires"><a href="https://wikitravel.org/en/Brescia">Italian Capital of Culture 2023</a></h3>
                                            <div class="info">
                                                <div class="info-holder">
                                                    <div class="info-frame">
                                                        <p>Together with Bergamo, Brescia was chosen as Italian capital of culture 2023. Among the many points of interests, Brescia's roman ruins and the nearby monastic complex are UNESCO World Heritage Site.</p>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>

                                                                            <div class="slide">
                                            <img src="//wikitravel.org/customHP/uploads/des_month/369_1697367325.jpg" alt="Argentinian Cuisine" />
                                            <h2 class="subHeading"><a href="https://wikitravel.org/en/Argentina#Eat">Cuisine of the Month</a></h2>
                                            <h3 class="buenos-aires"><a href="https://wikitravel.org/en/Argentina#Eat">Argentinian Cuisine</a></h3>
                                            <div class="info">
                                                <div class="info-holder">
                                                    <div class="info-frame">
                                                        <p>Beef is a prominent component of the Argentine diet and Argentine beef is world-famous for good reason. Argentina and Uruguay are the top 2 countries in the world in consumption of meat per capita.</p>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>

                                                                            <div class="slide">
                                            <img src="//wikitravel.org/customHP/uploads/des_month/370_1698508754.jpg" alt="Himeji Castle" />
                                            <h2 class="subHeading"><a href="https://wikitravel.org/en/Himeji">Landmark of the Month</a></h2>
                                            <h3 class="buenos-aires"><a href="https://wikitravel.org/en/Himeji">Himeji Castle</a></h3>
                                            <div class="info">
                                                <div class="info-holder">
                                                    <div class="info-frame">
                                                        <p>Have you heard of the ghost that haunts the castle? Do you dare to visit this Halloween?</p>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>

                                                                            <div class="slide">
                                            <img src="//wikitravel.org/customHP/uploads/des_month/367_1696873177.jpg" alt="Konkani" />
                                            <h2 class="subHeading"><a href="https://wikitravel.org/en/Konkani_phrasebook">Language of the Month</a></h2>
                                            <h3 class="buenos-aires"><a href="https://wikitravel.org/en/Konkani_phrasebook">Konkani</a></h3>
                                            <div class="info">
                                                <div class="info-holder">
                                                    <div class="info-frame">
                                                        <p>Konkani is the main language of Goa, India. It is commonly spoken in various dialects along the western coastline of India, from Damaon to Cochin</p>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
